Java 9 introduced the Java Platform Module System (JPMS). A module is a named, self-describing collection of packages declared in `module-info.java`.

```java
module com.example.app {
    requires java.base;
    exports com.example.app.api;
}
```

- `requires` — declares a dependency on another module
- `exports` — makes packages accessible to other modules
- `opens` — allows reflective access

Modules enforce strong encapsulation at the package level, beyond what `public`/`private` provide.

examples.code:
